text: The long jump event at the 1930 Women's World Games was held in Prague at the Letná Stadium, with the final being held on 8 September 1930. ==Entrants== In August 1930 entrants were published of the athletes of 5 nations: the Netherlands, Sweden, Switzerland, Italy and Great Britain. Listed below are the athletes from these nations who were entered for the long jump event. Nationality Name ==Results== ===Qualification=== ===Final=== The final took place in the morning of 8 September. Between sources there are some differences in the distances. This might be typo errors, or possibly a mix-up with the qualification.
